It includes Freeciv 2.3.1

If you don't need to change source code and don't need latest version simply download APK from http://civ.zielm.com

== DEPENDENCIES ==
Building Freeciv for Android is currently only possible on Linux. On Ubuntu/Debian you need:
   sudo apt-get install python-lzma python-tk python-pygame zlib1g-dev python2.7-dev

Then configure:
   bash ./build.sh

Build Freeciv for Android to run on desktop (for debugging):
   make -Csrc
   make -Cserver

And run:
   python main.py

Build Freeciv for Android for Android:
   android/zlib.sh
   android/debug.sh

APK which you can install on your device will be android/build/apk/FreecivDebug-0.9.0-debug.apk

